# Per-integration Neo4j secrets for the Finance Genie example.
#
# Copy this file to `.env` in this same directory and fill in the values. The
# populated .env is local-only; do not commit it.
#
# This file holds ONLY the NEO4J_* credentials. It is the single source of
# truth for this integration's Neo4j instance, consumed two ways:
#   - setup_secrets.sh reads it to provision the Databricks secret scope that
#     on-cluster ingest jobs read (the scope NAME lives in dbxcarta-overlay.env).
#   - off-cluster, the local dbxcarta-client reads only these NEO4J_* keys from
#     this file (via load_overlay_secrets) since the committed overlay is
#     secret-free.
#
# All non-secret config (catalogs, volume, schemas, embedding/sample flags,
# client arms, secret-scope name) lives in the committed ./dbxcarta-overlay.env.
# Do not add any other keys here; they would not be read and only risk drifting
# from the overlay.

NEO4J_URI=
NEO4J_USERNAME=
NEO4J_PASSWORD=
